FBIS4-9317 "dreeu079_i_94015" FBIS-EEU-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA NATO Extends Ultimatum To Other Safe Areas NATO Extends Ultimatum To Other Safe Areas LD2304025294 Belgrade TANJUG in English 0019 GMT 23 Apr 94 LD2304025294 Belgrade TANJUG English BFN ["Pool" item] [Text] Brussels, April 22 (TANJUG) -- The North Atlantic Council late on Friday night [22 April] extended its ultimatum to Bosnian Serbs to cmver the other U.N.-designated `safe havens' in Bosnia-Herzegovina. A statement released from the session said that Bosnian Serb armament would be targeted if they attacked the `safe havens' of Gorazde, Bihac, Srebrenica, Tuzla and Zepa from heavy weapons or in other ways. The towns were designated `safe havens' in spring of 1993.
